<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="26" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[835,1474,1795,2108]" lastBlockId="27.[813,1452,1671,1727]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="26" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,957,1795,1819]" pageId="26" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Both sexes: body sub-ovate, ventral surface with distinct dark marks; fore femur clearly longer than mesosternum. Male: fore femur moderately slender (ratio length/width: 5.66–6.49), proximal half about as wide as distal half, ventral surface with a distinct notch near the middle, pilosity denser and longer at proximal half (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="135">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
); genitalia of medium size, abdominal segment 8 clearly longer than sternum 7; pygophore simple, on ventral view apex of pygophore broadly rounded, postero-lateral surface with sparse long yellowish hairs; proctiger simple, slightly broadened at basal two-fifths, with long hairs on lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[292,388,1703,1728]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
); paramere not extending beyond genital segment but prominent, curved dorsad at distal half, apex broadened and rounded, curved outwards and posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[245,404,1799,1824]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Figs. 110–112</figureCitation>
); endosoma: dorsal sclerite long and recurved proximally, apical accessory sclerite large but weakly sclerotised, lateral sclerite slender and short, thin accessory lateral sclerite present (
<figureCitation box="[483,645,1895,1920]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Figs. 113, 114</figureCitation>
). Female: fore femur simple and slender (ratio length/width 6.94–7.53); hind trochanter elongated, without long hairs (
<figureCitation box="[639,738,1959,1983]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
); abdomen shortened, tip of abdomen not surpassing apex of hind trochanter; sternum 7 large, clearly longer than previous sterna together, constricted laterally, posterior part producing a median lobe with broadly rounded apical margin, directed dorsad, and completely enclosing genitalia on ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[822,918,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Fig. 116</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
